<paragraph id="8BEC369CFF86A426FF400FC0FED3F7F1" blockId="0.[136,1451,2025,2083]" pageId="0" pageNumber="291">
<taxonomicName id="4C534D1FFF86A426FF400FC0FE11F82C" box="[136,395,2025,2046]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balanophoraceae" genus="Balanophora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Santalales" pageId="0" pageNumber="291" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coralliformis">
<emphasis id="B927EA8EFF86A426FF400FC0FE11F82C" box="[136,395,2025,2046]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="291">Balanophora coralliformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from all other described 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D1FFF86A426FD0F0FC0FC08F82D" box="[711,914,2025,2047]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balanophoraceae" genus="Balanophora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Santalales" pageId="0" pageNumber="291" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B927EA8EFF86A426FD0F0FC0FCDCF82C" box="[711,838,2025,2046]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="291">Balanophora</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in the coral-like growth of repeatedly branched aboveground tubers.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC369CFF87A427FF7508B7FA9FFEBF" blockId="1.[136,1452,158,365]" pageId="1">
Also the poorly known 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D1FFF87A427FE7608B6FC5BFF0F" authority="(Eichler in De Candolle 1873: 145) Hansen (1972: 106)" authorityName="Hansen" authorityPageNumber="106" authorityYear="1972" baseAuthorityName="Eichler in De Candolle" baseAuthorityPageNumber="145" baseAuthorityYear="1873" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balanophoraceae" genus="Balanophora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Santalales" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="fungosa" subSpecies="indica" variety="minor">
<emphasis id="B927EA8EFF87A427FE7608B6FDAFFF6A" box="[446,565,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="1">B. fungosa</emphasis>
J.R. Forster &amp; G. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B6DFF87A427FD3208B6FC58FF6A" author="Forster, J. R. &amp; Forster, G." box="[762,962,158,185]" pageId="1" pagination="1 - 150" refId="ref1086" refString="Forster, J. R. &amp; Forster, G. (1775) Characteres generum plantarum. London, pp. 1 - 150. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 4448" type="book chapter" year="1775">Forster (1775: 99)</bibRefCitation>
ssp. 
<emphasis id="B927EA8EFF87A427FC3F08B7FBA7FF6A" box="[1015,1085,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="1">indica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B6DFF87A427FB8208B7FB66FF6A" author="Arnott, G. W." box="[1098,1276,158,184]" pageId="1" pagination="36 - 39" refId="ref971" refString="Arnott, G. W. (1838) Some account of the genus Langsdorffia. Annals of Natural History 2: 36 - 39. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222933809496649" type="journal article" year="1838">Arnott 1838: 37</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B6DFF87A427FAC108B6FF21FF0E" author="Hansen, B." pageId="1" pagination="1 - 196" refId="ref1154" refString="Hansen, B. (1972) The genus Balanophora J. R. &amp; G. Forster. A taxonomic monograph. Dansk Botanisk Arkiv 28: 1 - 196." type="journal article" year="1972">Hansen (1972: 100)</bibRefCitation>
var. 
<emphasis id="B927EA8EFF87A427FF3E08EAFEA3FF0E" box="[246,313,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="1">minor</emphasis>
(Eichler in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B6DFF87A427FE0B08EAFD54FF0F" author="De Candolle, A. L. P. P." box="[451,718,194,221]" pageId="1" pagination="117 - 150" refId="ref1063" refString="De Candolle, A. L. P. P. (1873) Balanophoraceae. Prodromus 17: 117 - 150." type="journal article" year="1873">De Candolle 1873: 145</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B6DFF87A427FD1708EAFC5BFF0F" author="Hansen, B." box="[735,961,194,221]" pageId="1" pagination="1 - 196" refId="ref1154" refString="Hansen, B. (1972) The genus Balanophora J. R. &amp; G. Forster. A taxonomic monograph. Dansk Botanisk Arkiv 28: 1 - 196." type="journal article" year="1972">Hansen (1972: 106)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from south 
<collectingCountry id="F344760CFF87A427FB8708EBFB11FF0E" box="[1103,1163,194,220]" name="India" pageId="1">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F344760CFF87A427FB5008EBFA90FF0E" box="[1176,1290,194,220]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="1">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F344760CFF87A427FA8008EBFA36FF0E" box="[1352,1452,194,220]" name="Thailand" pageId="1">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B6DFF87A427FF5808CFFEB3FED2" author="Hansen, B." box="[144,297,230,256]" pageId="1" pagination="1 - 196" refId="ref1154" refString="Hansen, B. (1972) The genus Balanophora J. R. &amp; G. Forster. A taxonomic monograph. Dansk Botanisk Arkiv 28: 1 - 196." type="journal article" year="1972">Hansen 1972</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B6DFF87A427FEFD08CFFE42FED2" author="Nickrent, D. L." box="[309,472,230,256]" pageId="1" refId="ref1393" refString="Nickrent, D. L. (1997 onwards) The parasitic plant connection. Available from: http: // www. parasiticplants. siu. edu." type="url" year="1997">Nickrent 1997</bibRefCitation>
onwards, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B6DFF87A427FD8708CFFD6BFED2" author="Su, H. - J. &amp; Murata, J. &amp; Hu, J. - M." box="[591,753,230,256]" pageId="1" pagination="317 - 326" refId="ref1545" refString="Su, H. - J., Murata, J. &amp; Hu, J. - M. (2012) Morphology and phylogenetics of two holoparasitic plants, Balanophora japonica and Balanophora yakushimensis (Balanophoraceae), and their hosts in Taiwan and Japan. Journal of Plant Research 125: 317 - 326. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10265 - 011 - 0447 - 5" type="journal article" year="2012">
Su 
<emphasis id="B927EA8EFF87A427FDBD08CEFD35FED2" box="[629,687,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="1">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
) is described as having elongated, cylindrical tuber segments (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B6DFF87A427FF580923FEBDFEF6" author="Hansen, B." box="[144,295,266,292]" pageId="1" pagination="1 - 196" refId="ref1154" refString="Hansen, B. (1972) The genus Balanophora J. R. &amp; G. Forster. A taxonomic monograph. Dansk Botanisk Arkiv 28: 1 - 196." type="journal article" year="1972">Hansen 1972</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B6DFF87A427FEFA0923FE4BFEF6" author="Su, H. - J. &amp; Murata, J. &amp; Hu, J. - M." box="[306,465,266,292]" pageId="1" pagination="317 - 326" refId="ref1545" refString="Su, H. - J., Murata, J. &amp; Hu, J. - M. (2012) Morphology and phylogenetics of two holoparasitic plants, Balanophora japonica and Balanophora yakushimensis (Balanophoraceae), and their hosts in Taiwan and Japan. Journal of Plant Research 125: 317 - 326. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10265 - 011 - 0447 - 5" type="journal article" year="2012">
Su 
<emphasis id="B927EA8EFF87A427FE9E0922FE14FEF6" box="[342,398,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="1">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
), but photos on the Parasitic Plant Connection website (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B6DFF87A427FBF70923FB78FEF6" author="Nickrent, D. L." box="[1087,1250,266,292]" pageId="1" refId="ref1393" refString="Nickrent, D. L. (1997 onwards) The parasitic plant connection. Available from: http: // www. parasiticplants. siu. edu." type="url" year="1997">Nickrent 1997</bibRefCitation>
onwards) suggest that these are subterranean. Furthermore, amongst others, the leaves of this 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D1FFF87A427FC190907FBDDFE9B" box="[977,1095,302,329]" pageId="1" rank="variety" variety="are">variety are</taxonomicName>
more numerous (15–35 vs. 4 or 5) and spirally arranged (vs. opposite), and the staminate flowers are actinomorphic (vs. bisymmetric).
</paragraph>
